# Maximum Subarray (Kadane's Algorithm)

## Basic Description

Find the maximum possible sum of any contiguous subarray using Kadane's Algorithm. The algorithm maintains a running sum and resets it whenever it becomes negative, while tracking the maximum sum encountered throughout the traversal.
//this question  can be solved with two variable no need of third variable max_element , u can dry run and understand

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int maxSubArray(vector<int>& nums) {
        long long currentSum = 0;
        long long maxSum = nums[0];

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            currentSum += nums[i];
            maxSum = max(maxSum, currentSum);

            if (currentSum < 0) {
                currentSum = 0;
            }
        }

        return maxSum;
    }
};
```

**Time Complexity:** `O(n)`

**Space Complexity:** `O(1)`
